1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:10,000
[English subtitles are available]

2
00:01:32,280 --> 00:01:40,640
[You are My Fateful Love]
[EP22]

3
00:01:54,519 --> 00:01:55,079
B.

4
00:02:58,080 --> 00:02:58,759
Mr. Xu.

5
00:04:18,720 --> 00:04:20,600
[Xu Huaisong chose B.]

6
00:04:23,399 --> 00:04:24,240
[What?]

7
00:04:24,920 --> 00:04:25,439
[No way.]

8
00:04:25,759 --> 00:04:26,800
[What is that supposed to mean?]

9
00:04:27,439 --> 00:04:28,319
[It means]

10
00:04:28,319 --> 00:04:29,360
[you're flattering yourself?]

11
00:06:05,399 --> 00:06:06,360
[What did you just send?]

12
00:06:16,879 --> 00:06:17,600
[Wrong text.]

13
00:06:18,120 --> 00:06:19,160
[So I deleted it.]

14
00:06:19,839 --> 00:06:20,480
[Sorry.]

15
00:06:21,680 --> 00:06:22,720
Wrong one?

16
00:06:38,079 --> 00:06:39,079
Pick up.

17
00:06:45,160 --> 00:06:46,560
Hey, Ruan Yu?

18
00:06:47,920 --> 00:06:48,519
Hey.

19
00:06:55,079 --> 00:06:55,319
Ruan Yu.

20
00:06:55,319 --> 00:06:56,519
I didn't see the message

21
00:06:56,519 --> 00:06:57,319
you just sent.

22
00:06:58,120 --> 00:06:58,959
What did you unsend?

23
00:07:04,759 --> 00:07:05,879
So why did you text back?

24
00:07:06,759 --> 00:07:07,560
That message just now,
wasn't from me.

25
00:07:11,519 --> 00:07:12,160
Just tell me first,
what did you unsend?

26
00:07:15,800 --> 00:07:18,000
Uh... nothing.

27
00:07:22,480 --> 00:07:23,199
Are you home?

28
00:08:36,919 --> 00:08:37,559
Ruan Yu.

29
00:08:47,320 --> 00:08:47,960
Hey,

30
00:09:01,200 --> 00:09:02,320
what's wrong?

31
00:09:15,039 --> 00:09:16,120
I just need to know

32
00:09:17,440 --> 00:09:18,639
what exactly you unsent.

33
00:09:33,000 --> 00:09:33,759
[I asked him,]

34
00:09:34,440 --> 00:09:35,720
[do you want a boyfriend?]

35
00:09:35,720 --> 00:09:36,559
[Meaning,]

36
00:09:36,919 --> 00:09:38,879
[A, what do you think of me,]

37
00:09:39,440 --> 00:09:40,159
[or B,]

38
00:09:40,799 --> 00:09:41,840
[I set you up with someone.]

39
00:09:42,960 --> 00:09:43,919
[He said B.]

40
00:09:49,639 --> 00:09:50,480
A and B,

41
00:09:51,759 --> 00:09:53,039
aren't they the same answer?

42
00:10:02,000 --> 00:10:03,120
Don't just stand there.

43
00:10:03,720 --> 00:10:04,840
Let me get you some slippers.

44
00:10:06,240 --> 00:10:06,919
Hey,

45
00:10:09,919 --> 00:10:10,799
you must be thirsty.

46
00:10:11,279 --> 00:10:12,399
I'll boil some water for you.

47
00:10:33,440 --> 00:10:35,279
[Code red. Calling Shen Mingying.]

48
00:10:36,600 --> 00:10:37,519
[Emergency.]

49
00:10:37,799 --> 00:10:38,799
[Requesting backup.]

50
00:10:39,919 --> 00:10:40,799
[This is not a drill.]

51
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:41,960
[I repeat,]
[this is not a drill.]

52
00:10:43,879 --> 00:10:44,480
So?

53
00:10:44,480 --> 00:10:45,720
Was I right or what?

54
00:10:45,879 --> 00:10:47,159
Did Xu Huaisong confess his feelings?

55
00:10:48,399 --> 00:10:49,120
Wait, what?

56
00:10:50,600 --> 00:10:51,960
Xu is actually gonna confess?

57
00:10:52,120 --> 00:10:52,799
He's the one confessing,

58
00:10:52,799 --> 00:10:53,919
why are you so excited?

59
00:10:59,360 --> 00:10:59,879
Hey.

60
00:11:00,440 --> 00:11:01,080
Maybe

61
00:11:02,759 --> 00:11:03,960
he already confessed.

62
00:11:04,360 --> 00:11:05,039
Wait, what?

63
00:11:09,440 --> 00:11:10,559
Hey, why do I hear

64
00:11:10,559 --> 00:11:11,679
a guy's voice over there?

65
00:11:12,840 --> 00:11:13,919
I'm just watching TV.

66
00:11:15,320 --> 00:11:15,799
So,

67
00:11:16,159 --> 00:11:17,519
how did you respond?

68
00:11:18,799 --> 00:11:20,320
If I knew,

69
00:11:20,960 --> 00:11:22,240
would I be hiding in the bathroom?

70
00:11:22,600 --> 00:11:23,559
You're such a coward.

71
00:11:23,679 --> 00:11:24,120
Look,

72
00:11:24,120 --> 00:11:25,279
just take a moment

73
00:11:25,639 --> 00:11:27,000
and ask yourself

74
00:11:27,000 --> 00:11:28,600
if you're really ready to be in a relationship.

75
00:11:29,039 --> 00:11:30,200
Earlier today, I was this close

76
00:11:30,679 --> 00:11:31,799
to just going for it.

77
00:11:32,679 --> 00:11:34,240
But then he replied,

78
00:11:35,559 --> 00:11:36,440
and suddenly

79
00:11:37,559 --> 00:11:38,440
I felt like

80
00:11:39,240 --> 00:11:40,879
one word from him, and my whole world collapses.

81
00:11:40,879 --> 00:11:41,840
That's so pathetic.

82
00:11:43,399 --> 00:11:44,840
I don't want him to lead me around by the nose.

83
00:11:45,120 --> 00:11:46,360
Then you lead him instead.

84
00:11:46,879 --> 00:11:48,159
How? How do I do that?

85
00:11:48,840 --> 00:11:49,600
You used to write romance novels

86
00:11:49,600 --> 00:11:51,080
remember?

87
00:11:51,080 --> 00:11:51,919
All those tricks and strategies,

88
00:11:51,919 --> 00:11:53,320
you knew them inside out.

89
00:11:53,840 --> 00:11:55,200
But when it comes to yourself, you freeze.

90
00:11:55,840 --> 00:11:57,440
Just act a little hard to get,

91
00:11:57,559 --> 00:11:58,320
keep your distance,
and take control,

92
00:11:58,879 --> 00:12:00,000
use all of them!

93
00:12:02,879 --> 00:12:03,519
Okay.

94
00:12:04,000 --> 00:12:04,480
Okay.

95
00:12:05,000 --> 00:12:05,720
Text me later.

96
00:12:16,440 --> 00:12:17,480
Take control.

97
00:12:25,720 --> 00:12:26,639
Look at you.

98
00:12:26,639 --> 00:12:27,679
He confesses,

99
00:12:27,679 --> 00:12:28,919
and you get this excited?

100
00:12:29,360 --> 00:12:30,679
Come on, that's normal.

101
00:12:30,679 --> 00:12:32,000
Ha, you made me jump!

102
00:12:39,679 --> 00:12:41,399
You breathe one word

103
00:12:41,399 --> 00:12:42,000
of what I said to her

104
00:12:42,000 --> 00:12:43,279
to Xu Huaisong, and you're dead.

105
00:12:44,279 --> 00:12:45,120
I swear

106
00:12:47,320 --> 00:12:48,120
I won't say a thing.

107
00:12:51,039 --> 00:12:51,799
Look,

108
00:12:52,840 --> 00:12:53,799
my bro's love life
can't depend on me

109
00:12:54,759 --> 00:12:56,600
alone, right?

110
00:12:56,840 --> 00:12:58,120
He's gotta learn

111
00:12:58,440 --> 00:12:59,399
to stand on his own.

112
00:13:00,320 --> 00:13:01,759
You know what they say

113
00:13:01,799 --> 00:13:03,360
a guy needs to be tested.

114
00:13:04,879 --> 00:13:05,799
I support you guys.

115
00:13:06,720 --> 00:13:07,440
You said it.
A promise is a promise.

116
00:13:10,320 --> 00:13:10,879
Fine.

117
00:13:11,480 --> 00:13:12,159
Then just wait.

118
00:13:18,039 --> 00:13:19,120
Don't tell me you got me

119
00:13:19,120 --> 00:13:20,559
some kind of gift,

120
00:13:20,559 --> 00:13:21,159
Mingying?

121
00:13:38,759 --> 00:13:40,120
Boyfriend Trial Contract.

122
00:13:41,960 --> 00:13:42,960
You're the one who said

123
00:13:44,759 --> 00:13:45,440
men

124
00:13:45,799 --> 00:13:47,840
need to be tested to be trusted.

125
00:13:49,679 --> 00:13:51,440
So how are you gonna do that?

126
00:13:54,759 --> 00:13:55,879
What, not up for it?

127
00:13:56,200 --> 00:13:57,519
A test? Sure.

128
00:13:57,919 --> 00:13:58,519
Alright.

129
00:13:58,919 --> 00:14:00,159
A trial boyfriend

130
00:14:00,159 --> 00:14:00,960
is still a boyfriend, right?

131
00:14:01,039 --> 00:14:02,000
No problem.

132
00:14:02,879 --> 00:14:03,480
I'll sign.
Don't rush.

133
00:14:04,360 --> 00:14:04,960
Read it carefully.

134
00:14:04,960 --> 00:14:06,080
No, no need.

135
00:14:06,240 --> 00:14:06,919
Got any ink pad?

136
00:14:07,759 --> 00:14:08,559
Let me thumbprint it.

137
00:14:08,559 --> 00:14:09,639
Otherwise it doesn't count.

138
00:14:26,519 --> 00:14:27,080
Thank you.

139
00:14:31,399 --> 00:14:32,440
Who used your WeChat

140
00:14:32,440 --> 00:14:33,480
and texted me back?

141
00:14:34,759 --> 00:14:35,799
Probably Ms. Lyu.

142
00:14:37,320 --> 00:14:38,440
I was just working late at the firm.

143
00:14:40,000 --> 00:14:40,600
Oh.

144
00:14:45,960 --> 00:14:46,919
Look,

145
00:14:48,440 --> 00:14:49,799
it's up to you.

146
00:14:53,039 --> 00:14:53,960
Why me?

147
00:14:55,480 --> 00:14:56,320
Aren't you mad?

148
00:14:59,200 --> 00:15:00,639
Someone else was on your WeChat.

149
00:15:01,120 --> 00:15:02,360
Shouldn't you be the one who's upset?

150
00:15:04,840 --> 00:15:05,399
Well,

151
00:15:08,080 --> 00:15:09,120
two options.

152
00:15:10,720 --> 00:15:11,799
Which one do you want?

153
00:15:21,039 --> 00:15:21,879
You know,

154
00:15:23,559 --> 00:15:25,279
among the top ten

155
00:15:25,279 --> 00:15:26,360
fastest land animals

156
00:15:27,159 --> 00:15:28,159
there's actually the hare.

157
00:15:30,120 --> 00:15:30,960
I didn't know that.

158
00:15:32,799 --> 00:15:34,879
Never really thought about it.

159
00:15:39,240 --> 00:15:40,639
They seem so timid,

160
00:15:41,159 --> 00:15:42,519
like easy prey.

161
00:15:43,320 --> 00:15:44,399
But when they run,

162
00:15:44,960 --> 00:15:46,559
they can hit fifty miles an hour,

163
00:15:47,480 --> 00:15:48,600
almost as fast as a lion.

164
00:15:50,960 --> 00:15:52,440
But in that top ten list,

165
00:15:53,960 --> 00:15:55,159
the fox doesn't even make it.

166
00:15:58,159 --> 00:15:58,879
What do you mean?

167
00:16:00,360 --> 00:16:01,159
Anyway,

168
00:16:09,039 --> 00:16:09,759
good night.

169
00:16:35,720 --> 00:16:36,679
[Guess the fox just needs to chase]

170
00:16:37,080 --> 00:16:38,440
[a little harder.]

171
00:16:53,679 --> 00:16:54,679
Where are we eating?

172
00:16:54,919 --> 00:16:56,039
That place up there looks good.

173
00:16:57,120 --> 00:16:57,919
Let's do that.
- I'm hungry.
- Okay.

174
00:17:14,319 --> 00:17:14,960
Hello?

175
00:17:15,440 --> 00:17:16,039
Yeah?

176
00:17:17,079 --> 00:17:18,039
I'm downstairs.

177
00:17:23,519 --> 00:17:24,079
Wait,
what are you doing here?

178
00:17:25,680 --> 00:17:26,680
I'm here to take you to work.

179
00:17:27,240 --> 00:17:28,440
Brought you breakfast too.

180
00:17:29,559 --> 00:17:30,319
Take your time.

181
00:17:30,839 --> 00:17:31,480
I'll wait.

182
00:17:36,759 --> 00:17:37,759
This is how fast
lawyers chase people?

183
00:17:39,119 --> 00:17:39,839
Crazy.

184
00:17:50,200 --> 00:17:50,680
Morning.
Morning.

185
00:17:57,240 --> 00:17:57,759
Get in.

186
00:18:09,960 --> 00:18:11,079
What'd you get me for breakfast?

187
00:18:12,920 --> 00:18:14,359
Soy milk and

188
00:18:14,960 --> 00:18:15,480
Shaomai.

189
00:18:17,880 --> 00:18:18,880
Egg yolk shaomai.

190
00:18:19,000 --> 00:18:20,000
I haven't had these in forever.

191
00:18:20,559 --> 00:18:22,160
The owner is from Su City.

192
00:18:22,519 --> 00:18:23,279
I tried it.
It's super authentic.

193
00:18:25,759 --> 00:18:26,759
But I don't remember

194
00:18:26,759 --> 00:18:27,920
any place around here selling them.

195
00:18:29,759 --> 00:18:31,200
You didn't go out of your way

196
00:18:31,319 --> 00:18:32,400
early in the morning to get these, did you?

197
00:18:33,000 --> 00:18:33,599
Not really.

198
00:18:34,759 --> 00:18:37,559
You really don't have to go that far.

199
00:18:38,680 --> 00:18:40,119
Well, the fox is slow,

200
00:18:40,799 --> 00:18:42,119
so he's gotta run a few extra steps, right?

201
00:18:49,480 --> 00:18:50,400
[Why do I feel like

202
00:18:51,000 --> 00:18:52,319
a rabbit walking into a fox's den?]

203
00:18:54,359 --> 00:18:55,000
Let's go.

204
00:19:12,720 --> 00:19:13,240
Oh,
I gotta head to a meeting

205
00:19:13,839 --> 00:19:15,200
at Huan Vision this afternoon.

206
00:19:16,440 --> 00:19:17,160
I'll drop you off.

207
00:19:17,799 --> 00:19:18,480
Nah, it's fine.

208
00:19:18,599 --> 00:19:19,839
Don't you have your own meeting?

209
00:19:21,759 --> 00:19:22,559
Gotta take this.

210
00:19:24,640 --> 00:19:25,200
Hello?

211
00:19:28,319 --> 00:19:28,920
Yeah?

212
00:19:33,200 --> 00:19:34,920
I'll head back to the US right away.

213
00:19:36,160 --> 00:19:36,759
Thank you.

214
00:19:42,279 --> 00:19:43,359
What's wrong?

215
00:19:44,000 --> 00:19:45,039
My dad's condition just got worse.

216
00:19:46,039 --> 00:19:47,119
I need to head back as soon as I can.

217
00:19:52,359 --> 00:19:53,400
Just focus on driving.

218
00:19:54,000 --> 00:19:54,799
Go get your passport.

219
00:19:55,079 --> 00:19:55,960
I'll book your flight.

220
00:19:57,240 --> 00:19:57,920
Phone password?

221
00:19:58,519 --> 00:19:59,039
Your birthday.

222
00:20:07,720 --> 00:20:08,480
The earliest flight

223
00:20:08,480 --> 00:20:09,720
to San Francisco

224
00:20:09,720 --> 00:20:11,000
is at 1:30 PM. That work?

225
00:20:11,640 --> 00:20:12,240
Yeah.

226
00:20:13,240 --> 00:20:14,000
Payment password?

227
00:20:14,480 --> 00:20:15,440
309017.

228
00:20:19,960 --> 00:20:20,519
Booked.

229
00:20:23,160 --> 00:20:23,839
Just drive safe.

230
00:20:37,160 --> 00:20:38,319
I already called a car for you.

231
00:20:39,000 --> 00:20:40,400
And don't worry about Pipi.

232
00:20:41,200 --> 00:20:42,039
I've got him.

233
00:20:47,440 --> 00:20:48,240
Take care of yourself.

234
00:21:25,920 --> 00:21:27,279
Your dad will be okay.

235
00:21:57,319 --> 00:21:58,279
Hey.

236
00:21:58,559 --> 00:21:59,519
What a coincidence.

237
00:21:59,559 --> 00:22:00,559
Yes.

238
00:22:00,839 --> 00:22:01,519
You don't even know

239
00:22:01,640 --> 00:22:02,559
that time the elevator broke down

240
00:22:02,559 --> 00:22:03,920
ended up being a good thing for me.

241
00:22:04,039 --> 00:22:05,400
I cried all my makeup off,

242
00:22:05,400 --> 00:22:06,720
so I just took it off.

243
00:22:07,000 --> 00:22:08,400
And Huan Vision ended up liking

244
00:22:08,400 --> 00:22:09,319
my bare face,
so they let me in.

245
00:22:10,880 --> 00:22:11,759
Congrats.

246
00:22:12,960 --> 00:22:13,720
Which floor?

247
00:22:14,799 --> 00:22:15,480
Same as you.

248
00:22:15,960 --> 00:22:16,799
You going to Huan Vision too?

249
00:22:17,279 --> 00:22:17,759
Yeah.

250
00:22:20,880 --> 00:22:21,359
Let's go.

251
00:22:23,279 --> 00:22:24,079
Ms. Lily Vale.

252
00:22:24,759 --> 00:22:25,319
Right this way.

253
00:22:31,599 --> 00:22:34,359
[Wow, it's really Ms. Lily Vale.]

254
00:22:35,279 --> 00:22:36,559
For this casting,

255
00:22:37,079 --> 00:22:38,519
it's not about fame or what's on your resume.

256
00:22:39,119 --> 00:22:40,960
It's just about how well you fit the role.

257
00:22:41,440 --> 00:22:43,079
We're only looking for actors

258
00:22:43,079 --> 00:22:44,160
who match the characters in this project.

259
00:22:44,759 --> 00:22:46,200
So everyone,

260
00:22:46,200 --> 00:22:47,039
just relax.

261
00:22:47,440 --> 00:22:49,079
Show us your best,

262
00:22:49,160 --> 00:22:50,160
most real self.

263
00:22:50,440 --> 00:22:51,240
That's it.

264
00:23:10,160 --> 00:23:10,799
It's chilly.

265
00:23:11,519 --> 00:23:12,400
Go to my office,

266
00:23:12,680 --> 00:23:14,160
grab that box of the good tea,

267
00:23:14,519 --> 00:23:15,720
and make everyone a hot cup.

268
00:23:18,400 --> 00:23:19,440
We've got some in the break room.

269
00:23:19,960 --> 00:23:20,960
I'll brew it there.

270
00:23:28,319 --> 00:23:29,759
I've been to so many auditions,

271
00:23:29,880 --> 00:23:31,279
but I've never seen a boss

272
00:23:31,279 --> 00:23:32,559
as straight up as Mr. Wei.

273
00:23:34,000 --> 00:23:34,799
Ruan Yu.

274
00:23:35,880 --> 00:23:36,480
Where's Huaisong?

275
00:23:37,119 --> 00:23:37,839
He's not here.
I came by myself today.

276
00:23:38,960 --> 00:23:39,880
Well,

277
00:23:40,240 --> 00:23:41,200
we can drop you off.

278
00:23:42,480 --> 00:23:43,119
It's fine.

279
00:23:43,240 --> 00:23:44,160
I've already got a car.

280
00:23:45,279 --> 00:23:46,960
Alright then. Stay safe.

281
00:23:47,039 --> 00:23:47,759
We're heading off.

282
00:23:48,720 --> 00:23:49,200
See you.
Bye.

283
00:23:54,680 --> 00:23:55,079
Hey.

284
00:24:01,519 --> 00:24:02,799
Are you still mad at me?

285
00:24:03,119 --> 00:24:04,000
I know I was wrong.

286
00:24:04,000 --> 00:24:05,480
I shouldn't have blamed you for going to that business dinner.

287
00:24:06,000 --> 00:24:06,720
I'm sorry, okay?
It's not your fault.

288
00:24:08,119 --> 00:24:09,400
It's your boss. I know.

289
00:24:13,079 --> 00:24:13,759
[Just landed.]

290
00:24:14,400 --> 00:24:15,440
[Heading to the hospital now.]

291
00:24:40,920 --> 00:24:41,599
Before your father

292
00:24:41,599 --> 00:24:42,799
had the stroke,

293
00:24:42,920 --> 00:24:43,960
he was looking at this photo.

294
00:24:44,279 --> 00:24:45,680
He was still holding it when he passed out.

295
00:25:04,400 --> 00:25:05,079
Doctor Ross.

296
00:25:05,839 --> 00:25:06,799
How is my father?

297
00:25:07,839 --> 00:25:09,160
Mr. Xu is much better now.

298
00:25:09,920 --> 00:25:10,480
Don't worry.

299
00:25:12,279 --> 00:25:13,000
Thank you.

300
00:25:22,079 --> 00:25:23,440
[He's out of danger for now.]

301
00:25:24,839 --> 00:25:25,480
[That's a relief.]

302
00:25:30,839 --> 00:25:31,759
[I checked with the doctor.]

303
00:25:32,039 --> 00:25:33,720
[He'll need to be observed after surgery.]

304
00:25:34,359 --> 00:25:35,200
[So I'm guessing]

305
00:25:35,480 --> 00:25:37,000
[I'll be stuck in the US for a while.]

306
00:25:37,839 --> 00:25:39,359
[That law firm stuff you needed to do for your book,]

307
00:25:39,799 --> 00:25:40,759
[I gave it to Liu Mao.]

308
00:25:43,880 --> 00:25:44,440
Don't worry.

309
00:25:44,720 --> 00:25:45,960
I'll figure it out on my own.

310
00:25:46,400 --> 00:25:47,480
Stop worrying about me for now.

311
00:25:47,839 --> 00:25:48,920
Just focus on your dad.

312
00:25:56,240 --> 00:25:57,200
It's gonna be fine.

313
00:25:58,119 --> 00:25:58,680
It'll be okay.

314
00:26:10,960 --> 00:26:12,160
Pipi,

315
00:26:12,400 --> 00:26:13,519
guess what?

316
00:26:13,839 --> 00:26:14,359
you're gonna hang out with me

317
00:26:14,359 --> 00:26:16,119
for a little while, okay?

318
00:26:16,839 --> 00:26:17,319
Look,

319
00:26:17,640 --> 00:26:19,200
I just wrote a new chapter.

320
00:26:19,920 --> 00:26:21,519
Wanna see it?

321
00:26:22,440 --> 00:26:22,920
Here.

322
00:26:26,200 --> 00:26:27,039
[Grandma, look!]

323
00:26:27,039 --> 00:26:28,200
[The novel you're following is back!]

324
00:26:28,200 --> 00:26:29,079
[Tell everyone!]

325
00:26:29,079 --> 00:26:30,200
[My happiness is back!]

326
00:26:30,240 --> 00:26:31,599
[Welcome back, Ms. Lily Vale!]

327
00:26:52,359 --> 00:26:53,519
[Going to sleep. Morning.]

328
00:27:28,759 --> 00:27:30,680
[Just woke up. Night.]

329
00:28:09,200 --> 00:28:09,920
[Have you eaten?]

330
00:28:10,640 --> 00:28:11,279
[Making it now.]

331
00:28:22,519 --> 00:28:23,319
[I'm up.]

332
00:28:35,079 --> 00:28:36,759
Pipi, say hi.

333
00:28:37,200 --> 00:28:38,160
Say hi.

334
00:28:38,599 --> 00:28:39,680
Look how lively our Pipi is.

335
00:28:39,680 --> 00:28:40,319
See that?

336
00:28:40,559 --> 00:28:41,640
He even stood up.

337
00:28:41,920 --> 00:28:42,839
What a good boy.
Pipi.

338
00:28:44,119 --> 00:28:45,119
How are you even cuter today, Pipi?
Look over here.

339
00:28:46,039 --> 00:28:47,000
He misses you.
Look at our Pipi.

340
00:28:47,960 --> 00:28:48,839
He's so tough.

341
00:28:49,119 --> 00:28:50,279
So healthy.

342
00:28:50,279 --> 00:28:51,400
And this cute.

343
00:28:52,599 --> 00:28:53,119
Well,
did you rest well?

344
00:29:27,000 --> 00:29:28,319
[The trial went well.]

345
00:30:39,200 --> 00:30:41,119
Still no update?

346
00:30:43,680 --> 00:30:44,640
Come on.

347
00:30:45,119 --> 00:30:46,079
Stop waiting for it.
If you don't eat now,

348
00:30:46,640 --> 00:30:47,920
that food in front of you is what really needs an update.

349
00:30:48,359 --> 00:30:49,759
I'm waiting for my literary fix.

350
00:30:50,480 --> 00:30:52,119
Ruan Yu's novel

351
00:30:52,119 --> 00:30:53,480
is hitting the final chapter today.

352
00:30:53,839 --> 00:30:54,759
It is called
Graduation Trip.

353
00:30:56,079 --> 00:30:58,119
do you think it's gonna be a bad ending

354
00:30:58,119 --> 00:30:59,039
or a happy one?

355
00:31:01,599 --> 00:31:02,480
Well,

356
00:31:03,079 --> 00:31:04,079
if it's realistic,
it'll probably be sad.

357
00:31:05,359 --> 00:31:05,920
Otherwise you'd already have
a sister-in-law by now.

358
00:31:06,960 --> 00:31:07,720
Your nieces and nephews

359
00:31:07,720 --> 00:31:08,759
would be running around already.

360
00:31:09,519 --> 00:31:10,640
What if it's not realistic?

361
00:31:11,160 --> 00:31:12,319
I think there's gonna be a twist.

362
00:31:13,079 --> 00:31:13,680
Fine, fine.
Go on then,

363
00:31:14,160 --> 00:31:15,119
wait for the new chapter.

364
00:31:15,359 --> 00:31:16,519
This is good. Try a bite.

365
00:31:20,880 --> 00:31:21,759
Stop it.

366
00:31:22,000 --> 00:31:23,000
Never seen two bros
feeding each other?

367
00:31:24,000 --> 00:31:25,359
Never.

368
00:31:26,839 --> 00:31:27,880
Okay okay, I give up.

369
00:31:33,079 --> 00:31:33,599
Get out of here.

370
00:31:35,000 --> 00:31:35,839
It is pretty good.

371
00:31:41,079 --> 00:31:42,279
It's the final chapter! It's the final chapter!

372
00:32:23,599 --> 00:32:24,960
[Going to sleep. Morning.]

373
00:32:25,920 --> 00:32:27,359
[Just woke up. Night.]

374
00:32:29,039 --> 00:32:30,799
[I'm up. Night.]

375
00:32:32,119 --> 00:32:32,839
[Have you eaten?]

376
00:32:33,920 --> 00:32:35,359
[Making it now. You?]

377
00:32:36,680 --> 00:32:37,640
[Just had a quick meal.]

378
00:32:46,279 --> 00:32:47,599
[I just finished the ending of my novel.]

379
00:32:48,160 --> 00:32:50,279
[The cherry blossoms in Hang City are blooming too.]

380
00:32:58,200 --> 00:32:59,160
[This is Lyu Shenglan.]

381
00:32:59,680 --> 00:33:00,680
[Got time to meet up?]

382
00:33:06,440 --> 00:33:08,000
You look well, Ms. Ruan.

383
00:33:09,720 --> 00:33:11,519
You flew all the way here to see me,

384
00:33:12,200 --> 00:33:13,359
so I'm guessing it's not just

385
00:33:13,359 --> 00:33:14,559
to tell me that.

386
00:33:16,720 --> 00:33:18,400
Okay, you like it straight.

387
00:33:18,720 --> 00:33:19,519
I'll be blunt.

388
00:33:21,960 --> 00:33:22,799
Huaisong's been back in the States
for over a month now.

389
00:33:24,960 --> 00:33:25,759
Do you even know how he's been

390
00:33:25,759 --> 00:33:26,799
getting by?

391
00:33:30,640 --> 00:33:31,759
He's at the hospital with his dad,

392
00:33:31,759 --> 00:33:32,680
taking care of him,

393
00:33:33,400 --> 00:33:34,640
while trying to keep up with work,

394
00:33:34,759 --> 00:33:35,519
and on top of that, getting ready
for multiple trials.

395
00:33:36,680 --> 00:33:37,240
All that alone

396
00:33:37,240 --> 00:33:38,279
is already a lot for him.

397
00:33:39,039 --> 00:33:40,000
And still, with the time difference,
he calls you,

398
00:33:41,279 --> 00:33:42,160
talks to you.

399
00:33:43,000 --> 00:33:43,759
Don't you feel

400
00:33:43,759 --> 00:33:44,839
that you're just nothing

401
00:33:46,079 --> 00:33:46,680
but a burden

402
00:33:46,680 --> 00:33:48,039
and a distraction to him?

403
00:33:51,640 --> 00:33:52,440
Ms. Lyu,

404
00:33:52,680 --> 00:33:53,839
what makes you think

405
00:33:53,839 --> 00:33:54,799
you get to say all this?

406
00:33:55,599 --> 00:33:56,480
Whether I'm a burden or not

407
00:33:56,920 --> 00:33:58,119
is not for someone else

408
00:33:58,759 --> 00:33:59,480
to decide.
And you're definitely

409
00:34:00,319 --> 00:34:01,440
not the one to judge.

410
00:34:08,519 --> 00:34:09,239
You're right.

411
00:34:09,880 --> 00:34:11,159
I don't have a say in this.

412
00:34:12,079 --> 00:34:12,599
But I've seen a side of him
you've never seen.

413
00:34:14,599 --> 00:34:15,840
I know what it cost him

414
00:34:15,840 --> 00:34:17,119
to get where he is in the States.

415
00:34:18,000 --> 00:34:18,800
So I think I at least have
the right to say that.

416
00:34:29,440 --> 00:34:30,880
You do realize,

417
00:34:33,119 --> 00:34:33,840
a Chinese person

418
00:34:33,840 --> 00:34:35,119
trying to make it in a top tier industry over there,

419
00:34:35,119 --> 00:34:36,199
that's not easy.

420
00:34:36,639 --> 00:34:37,880
It's really not.

421
00:34:38,360 --> 00:34:39,039
They don't go easy on you

422
00:34:39,039 --> 00:34:40,559
just because you're from somewhere else.

423
00:34:41,119 --> 00:34:41,760
If anything,

424
00:34:42,880 --> 00:34:43,360
they judge you
even more harshly.

425
00:34:44,280 --> 00:34:45,039
That's just how it is.

426
00:34:45,880 --> 00:34:46,679
Back then, he graduated

427
00:34:46,679 --> 00:34:48,039
with the best grades

428
00:34:48,039 --> 00:34:48,719
in the whole year.

429
00:34:50,599 --> 00:34:51,440
For years,

430
00:34:52,280 --> 00:34:53,360
he was looked down on,

431
00:34:53,679 --> 00:34:54,559
doubted,

432
00:34:54,840 --> 00:34:55,760
until he finally proved himself,

433
00:34:55,760 --> 00:34:57,119
and everyone had to eat their words.

434
00:34:59,039 --> 00:34:59,960
During that time,

435
00:35:01,400 --> 00:35:02,400
he collapsed from overwork

436
00:35:02,719 --> 00:35:03,679
and ended up in the hospital twice.

437
00:35:05,639 --> 00:35:06,960
Doctors told him

438
00:35:07,440 --> 00:35:08,800
he couldn't keep burning the candle at both ends.

439
00:35:10,599 --> 00:35:11,840
Then not long after he started practicing,

440
00:35:12,679 --> 00:35:14,280
his father had a stroke,

441
00:35:14,920 --> 00:35:16,800
went from being a top lawyer

442
00:35:17,719 --> 00:35:19,119
to losing his ability to care for himself overnight.

443
00:35:19,800 --> 00:35:20,719
He became forgetful,
almost like dementia.

444
00:35:22,880 --> 00:35:23,960
And Huaisong, without a word,

445
00:35:23,960 --> 00:35:25,039
took over all the cases

446
00:35:25,039 --> 00:35:26,000
his father left behind.

447
00:35:27,239 --> 00:35:27,800
He faced all the

448
00:35:27,800 --> 00:35:29,079
mistrust from the clients,

449
00:35:30,039 --> 00:35:31,239
worked day and night,

450
00:35:32,800 --> 00:35:33,119
and in the end,

451
00:35:33,119 --> 00:35:34,519
he won every single case.

452
00:35:44,840 --> 00:35:45,400
Sometimes

453
00:35:45,400 --> 00:35:46,679
I just don't get it.

454
00:35:48,679 --> 00:35:49,559
What kind of belief

455
00:35:49,559 --> 00:35:50,760
does a person have

456
00:35:51,559 --> 00:35:52,360
that keeps him going
to such extremes?

457
00:35:55,679 --> 00:35:56,480
But it doesn't seem to be

458
00:35:56,480 --> 00:35:57,599
just a sense of duty,

459
00:35:59,679 --> 00:36:01,000
nor just

460
00:36:02,800 --> 00:36:03,800
professional ambition.

461
00:36:07,320 --> 00:36:08,119
I still haven't figured out
the answer,

462
00:36:11,760 --> 00:36:12,760
but I do know

463
00:36:13,960 --> 00:36:15,280
how precious everything is

464
00:36:15,280 --> 00:36:16,559
that he earned

465
00:36:16,559 --> 00:36:18,039
by pushing himself to the limit.

466
00:36:21,039 --> 00:36:22,360
And now you're about to ruin it.

467
00:36:40,920 --> 00:36:42,559
If he's really willing to give up everything in the States

468
00:36:42,559 --> 00:36:44,480
and come back for you,

469
00:36:46,000 --> 00:36:47,239
can you accept that sacrifice

470
00:36:47,239 --> 00:36:48,400
with a clear conscience?

471
00:36:49,400 --> 00:36:50,360
Or maybe

472
00:36:51,559 --> 00:36:52,320
his feelings for you

473
00:36:52,320 --> 00:36:53,840
aren't that deep after all.

474
00:36:55,199 --> 00:36:56,679
Like you two are now,

475
00:36:56,800 --> 00:36:57,239
with all that time difference,

476
00:36:57,239 --> 00:36:58,760
not even being able to

477
00:36:58,880 --> 00:36:59,639
say good night

478
00:36:59,639 --> 00:37:01,119
at the same time,

479
00:37:01,719 --> 00:37:02,599
how long do you think
a relationship like that can last?

480
00:37:42,800 --> 00:37:43,880
Why on earth

481
00:37:43,880 --> 00:37:45,440
do you make such mistakes?

482
00:37:51,719 --> 00:37:52,679
That's Xu Huaisong.

483
00:37:52,760 --> 00:37:53,559
The other one who got a perfect score.

484
00:38:01,599 --> 00:38:02,480
Group project.

485
00:38:02,639 --> 00:38:03,559
Team up with me.

486
00:38:04,159 --> 00:38:05,119
I don't need a team.

487
00:38:05,400 --> 00:38:06,039
You just don't need

488
00:38:06,039 --> 00:38:07,119
to team up with anyone worse than you.

489
00:38:21,599 --> 00:38:22,320
Okay.

490
00:38:22,639 --> 00:38:23,480
We're done here.

491
00:38:23,719 --> 00:38:24,559
- Okay.
- Fine.

492
00:38:28,840 --> 00:38:29,280
Bye.

493
00:38:30,960 --> 00:38:31,920
Heard you got the offer.

494
00:38:32,239 --> 00:38:32,840
Xu Huaisong's dad
is gonna be your

495
00:38:33,320 --> 00:38:34,079
supervising attorney, right?

496
00:38:34,400 --> 00:38:35,039
Yeah.

497
00:38:36,639 --> 00:38:38,159
So many firms in San Francisco,

498
00:38:38,360 --> 00:38:39,440
and you just happened to apply

499
00:38:39,440 --> 00:38:40,280
to the same one as him.

500
00:38:40,800 --> 00:38:41,679
You like him, don't you?

501
00:38:43,079 --> 00:38:44,159
Took you till graduation

502
00:38:44,440 --> 00:38:45,400
to figure that out?

503
00:38:48,360 --> 00:38:49,199
Well,

504
00:38:49,400 --> 00:38:50,599
staring at a face like that every day

505
00:38:50,599 --> 00:38:51,440
while working on projects,

506
00:38:51,440 --> 00:38:52,519
it's pretty hard not to fall for him.

507
00:38:53,519 --> 00:38:54,559
Let me correct you.

508
00:38:54,960 --> 00:38:56,199
It's not his face I like.

509
00:38:57,800 --> 00:38:58,440
Sure.
You

510
00:38:59,119 --> 00:39:00,800
only likes the strong ones, right?

511
00:39:01,760 --> 00:39:02,519
So let me ask you.

512
00:39:02,840 --> 00:39:04,079
There are two choices.

513
00:39:04,880 --> 00:39:06,840
A, you get to be with him

514
00:39:07,000 --> 00:39:07,639
but

515
00:39:07,960 --> 00:39:09,159
he ends up wasting

516
00:39:09,159 --> 00:39:11,039
all his talent and career.

517
00:39:11,400 --> 00:39:12,360
Every bit of it.

518
00:39:13,000 --> 00:39:13,599
B,

519
00:39:13,719 --> 00:39:15,239
you never get to be with him,

520
00:39:15,239 --> 00:39:16,079
ever,

521
00:39:16,559 --> 00:39:17,199
but he

522
00:39:17,199 --> 00:39:19,199
stays brilliant and strong forever.

523
00:39:19,599 --> 00:39:20,320
Which one do you pick?

524
00:39:21,159 --> 00:39:22,360
What a stupid question.

525
00:39:22,360 --> 00:39:23,000
I'm out of here.

526
00:39:31,719 --> 00:39:32,480
I'd pick B.

527
00:40:31,239 --> 00:40:32,000
Who is it?

528
00:40:35,320 --> 00:40:35,920
Coming.

529
00:40:41,480 --> 00:40:43,159
Hey, sis.

530
00:40:43,639 --> 00:40:44,320
What's up?

531
00:40:46,920 --> 00:40:47,679
You okay?

532
00:40:49,000 --> 00:40:49,960
Sis,
I read the last chapter

533
00:40:50,960 --> 00:40:52,119
yesterday,

534
00:40:52,119 --> 00:40:53,800
and I've been wanting to cry ever since.

535
00:40:55,360 --> 00:40:56,760
Why did it have to end like that?

536
00:40:57,320 --> 00:40:58,280
You almost

537
00:40:58,280 --> 00:40:59,920
confessed to my brother.

538
00:41:03,800 --> 00:41:04,760
You know

539
00:41:05,800 --> 00:41:07,440
I was writing about your brother, right?

540
00:41:10,119 --> 00:41:12,599
I've known for a while actually.

541
00:41:13,480 --> 00:41:15,480
Hey, don't be sad.

542
00:41:16,039 --> 00:41:17,920
There's a reason

543
00:41:17,920 --> 00:41:19,079
he left back then.

544
00:41:21,000 --> 00:41:21,920
I know.

545
00:41:23,400 --> 00:41:24,840
He never talks,

546
00:41:25,079 --> 00:41:26,239
so you definitely don't know

547
00:41:26,400 --> 00:41:27,760
what really happened in my family.

548
00:41:28,719 --> 00:41:30,159
Wasn't it because of your parents?

549
00:41:30,679 --> 00:41:32,039
They did get divorced,

550
00:41:32,559 --> 00:41:34,280
but not

551
00:41:34,280 --> 00:41:35,440
because they didn't get along.

552
00:41:35,719 --> 00:41:36,440
[My mom and dad]

553
00:41:36,440 --> 00:41:37,599
[split up]

554
00:41:37,840 --> 00:41:39,719
[because she didn't like his job.]

555
00:41:42,480 --> 00:41:43,360
My dad

556
00:41:44,199 --> 00:41:46,119
used to be a criminal defense lawyer.

557
00:41:46,480 --> 00:41:48,239
He defended murderers a lot.

558
00:41:48,920 --> 00:41:49,800
Then one time,

559
00:41:49,800 --> 00:41:51,079
he took on a case

560
00:41:51,519 --> 00:41:52,119
where a suspect

561
00:41:52,119 --> 00:41:53,599
accused of murder

562
00:41:53,719 --> 00:41:54,920
got off.

563
00:41:57,079 --> 00:41:57,840
From the moment

564
00:41:57,840 --> 00:41:59,280
we took that case,

565
00:42:00,039 --> 00:42:01,599
my mom never really understood him.

566
00:42:02,039 --> 00:42:04,719
There was always fighting at home.

567
00:42:05,800 --> 00:42:06,400
Then,

568
00:42:07,159 --> 00:42:08,639
after the suspect was released,

569
00:42:08,639 --> 00:42:10,320
things got way worse.

570
00:42:11,039 --> 00:42:13,000
The neighbors all talked behind our backs.

571
00:42:13,320 --> 00:42:14,199
The victim's family

572
00:42:14,199 --> 00:42:15,840
kept showing up at our door,

573
00:42:16,440 --> 00:42:18,280
throwing paint, smashing eggs.

574
00:42:19,119 --> 00:42:20,400
They even called my dad

575
00:42:21,480 --> 00:42:22,880
an accomplice to a killer.

576
00:42:25,599 --> 00:42:27,320
I was so young

577
00:42:29,239 --> 00:42:30,599
and got scared.

578
00:42:31,320 --> 00:42:32,960
So after they got divorced,

